---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/ui/Header.astro";
---

<Layout title="The Quorum | Agora" description="The strategic and theoretical core of the Agora movement.">
  
  <article class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6 bg-olive-50 text-olive-900 antialiased">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-16">

      <Header>
        <span slot="surtitle">
          Internal Governance
        </span>
        <fragment slot="header">
          Quorum
        </fragment>
        <fragment slot="subtitle">
          The ideological vanguard and political leadership of a growing movement.
        </fragment>
      </Header>

      <hr class="border-olive-200" />

      <section class="space-y-6">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-olive-950">What is Quorum?</h2>
        <p class="text-olive-800 leading-relaxed text-lg">
          If you are a member of Agora who has proven your reliability, responsibility, and dedication to our community, your Sponsor may recommend you for appointment to the <strong class="text-amber-700">Quorum</strong>.
        </p>
        <p class="text-olive-800 leading-relaxed">
          This is the core organizing body of our movement. As a member of Quorum, you take on greater responsibilities for the project’s health, gaining the right to vote on the leadership and strategic direction of Agora.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="p-8 bg-white border border-olive-200 rounded-3xl shadow-sm space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-olive-950">The Strategic Compass</h2>
        <p class="text-olive-800 leading-relaxed">
          While Agora is distributed at the chapter level, the <strong class="text-amber-700">Quorum</strong> oversees our political organizing.
        </p>
        <p class="text-olive-800 leading-relaxed">
          The Quorum is not a ruling body, but a <strong>political vanguard</strong>. Its authority is derived from its responsibility to the movement's goals and democratic decisions of our members.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="grid gap-6">
        <div class="p-8 bg-olive-900 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border-l-4 border-amber-500 space-y-4">
          <h3 class="text-amber-400 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-mono">1. Political Education</h3>
          <p class="text-olive-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Developing the curriculum for our political study circles. The Quorum translates critiques of privatization and neoliberalism into actionable knowledge for the community.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-olive-900 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border-l-4 border-amber-500 space-y-4">
          <h3 class="text-amber-400 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-mono">2. Campaign Strategy</h3>
          <p class="text-olive-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Identifying strategic targets for political action. The Quorum coordinates pressure campaigns against political and corporate targets, as well as "offline days of action" to maximize the movement's visibility.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="p-8 bg-olive-900 rounded-2xl shadow-xl border-l-4 border-amber-500 space-y-4">
          <h3 class="text-amber-400 font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-xs font-mono">3. Project Security</h3>
          <p class="text-olive-100 text-sm leading-relaxed">
            Maintaining the app infrastructure. Quorum manages the development of the Agora platform and ensures the security of member data.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="space-y-6 pt-12 border-t border-olive-200">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-olive-950">How the Quorum Forms</h2>
        <p class="text-olive-800 leading-relaxed">
          Membership to Quorum is granted not through a simple application process, but offered to members who display a proven track record of <strong class="text-amber-700">responsible leadership</strong>. It is composed of the movement's most active organizers who have successfully sustained local chapters for a period of no less than two years.
        </p>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
          <span class="w-2 h-2 rounded-full bg-amber-500 animate-pulse"></span>
          <p class="text-olive-500 font-mono text-[10px] uppercase tracking-widest">
            Status: Active // Members: Undisclosed for security
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="p-8 bg-white border border-olive-200 rounded-3xl shadow-sm space-y-4">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-olive-950">A Philosophical Foundation</h2>
        <p class="text-olive-800 leading-relaxed">
          Many of Quorum’s founding organizers met as members of the <strong class="text-amber-700">Adelphosophical Society</strong>, a spiritual and philosophical reading group from which many of the founding tenets of the Agora Project were based. Follow the link below to learn more about this underappreciated and oft-misunderstood school of thought.
        </p>
        <div class="text-center pt-4">
        <a href="/philosophy" class="inline-block bg-amber-600 text-white px-10 py-4 rounded-full font-bold hover:bg-amber-700 transition shadow-lg shadow-amber-600/20 active:scale-95 text-sm uppercase tracking-widest">
          Find out more
        </a>
      </div>
      </section>

      <footer class="pt-12">
        <a href="/manifesto" class="text-olive-600 hover:text-amber-700 font-bold transition flex items-center gap-2 group">
          <span class="group-hover:-translate-x-1 transition-transform">←</span> Back to the Manifesto
        </a>
      </footer>

    </div>
  </article>

</Layout>